{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: failure is at a module handoff boundary (three collectors -> aggregator/payload builder), not a single pure function. REAL-INFRA: no real OS/network/subprocess is required to catch omission/merge bugs; in-process fakes for the three sources are sufficient. MOCK-HIDE: mocking does not inherently hide this failure as long as each source returns distinct markers and the assembled payload is asserted. LLM-DEP: disqualified by behavior text ('content passed to the summary-generation step'); this checks pre-generation payload, not model judgment. MULTI-STEP: no multi-agentic chain.","test_description":"Wire real collection/orchestration modules with fake adapters for metrics, issue tracker, and deployment log; return unique sentinel values from each; assert the exact payload handed to summary generation contains all three sections/keys.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: this is cross-module error propagation/fallback (source adapter failure -> report assembler continues). REAL-INFRA: no need for real network outages; a source adapter raising timeout/5xx in-process reproduces the decision boundary. MOCK-HIDE: a mock can hide failure only if it never fails; configure one adapter to fail explicitly. LLM-DEP: disqualified by behavior text focusing on fallback note and non-abort behavior, not summary quality. MULTI-STEP: no chained model decisions.","test_description":"Run orchestration with two successful source adapters and one failing adapter; verify process completes, output includes `data unavailable` for only that section, and no global abort/exception occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.09,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"LLM-DEP: correctness depends on model output quality ('accurately represents'). A deterministic stub would always pass and cannot detect hallucination/omission/misstatement. MOCK-HIDE: replacing the model hides real failures in representation fidelity. REAL-INFRA: system-level transport checks are insufficient because the risk is semantic correctness of generated text. MULTI-STEP: behavior describes one generation judgment, not a multi-agent pipeline.","test_description":"Feed representative real input datasets to the actual summary model/prompt and evaluate generated narratives against key-value fidelity criteria (must include/align with specified metrics/issues/deploy facts) across repeated runs/tolerance rules.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.84,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: behavior explicitly requires end-to-end delivery to an inbox, which depends on real HTTP/API/subprocess/network/email infrastructure. Integration fakes can miss SMTP/API auth, routing, MIME, and delivery-path failures. LLM-DEP considered but rejected: behavior text is delivery outcome ('reaches ... inbox correctly'), not model decision quality; summary step can be deterministic for this test. MULTI-STEP agentic chain not required.","test_description":"Execute the scheduled/report pipeline against real reachable services (or production-like test endpoints) and a real mailbox; verify recipient receives one correctly addressed message with expected report artifact/body.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.82,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"REAL-INFRA: failure mode combines unreachable delivery service plus filesystem persistence plus next-run scheduler behavior; real OS/file/network boundaries are central. Integration fakes can miss path/permissions/atomic write/timing/run-to-run state issues. LLM-DEP: disqualified by behavior text (transport fallback/retry), not model content quality. MULTI-STEP agentic orchestration is not part of this behavior.","test_description":"Simulate real email endpoint unreachability during a run; assert report file is persisted on local disk; trigger the next scheduled execution and verify retry sends the saved report successfully and clears/marks pending state.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.83,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.04}}]}
